        <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="2">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid personal injury, always wear safety glasses, set the parking brakes and block the
                        wheels when working under a vehicle.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place transmission shift control lever into neutral position.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove cotter key and flat washer from the transmission shift cable swivel block at the
                    transmission end.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove jam nut from the end of the shift cable and screw off the swivel block.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the two screws attaching the shift cable clamp to the bracket on the side of the
                    transmission.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove sleeve seal (cut off with a sharp knife) and discard (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9813011">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f9813011" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g9813011" filename="../tsifigures/G9813011.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install one plastic washer (screw onto threaded portion of cable) until it bottoms at
                    the end of the threads (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9813011">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Spray lower end of cable liberally with WD 40 or equivalent while an assistant moves the
                    shift lever through all gear positions. Return the shift lever to the neutral position.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install boot over the end of the cable until it is in contact with the previously
                    installed washer in Step 6.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the second plastic washer until it is tight against the boot seal (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9813012">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f9813012" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g9813012" filename="../tsifigures/G9813012.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                    <caption>Figure 2.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Pull the other end (tubular end) of the boot until the raised ring in the boot is in
                    line with the groove in the cable where the sleeve seal was removed in Step 5. Secure with the
                    provided tie strap - be sure the locking side of the tie strap is positioned to the outside (away
                    from the transmission) (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9813012">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install the cable clamp (removed in Step 4).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install the swivel joint and lock nut and adjust as required.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install the flat washer and cotter key.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
